 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: I need to find P(Y₇ < 27.3), where Y₇ is the 7th order statistic out of 8 observations, and 27.3 is the 70th percentile of the distribution.

**Key Information:**
- We have 8 independent observations: Y₁ < Y₂ < ... < Y₈
- The 70th percentile is π₀.₇ = 27.3
- This means P(X < 27.3) = 0.70 for any single observation

**Finding P(Y₇ < 27.3):**

The event {Y₇ < 27.3} means that at least 7 of the 8 observations are less than 27.3.

Equivalently, {Y₇ < 27.3} means that the 7th order statistic is less than 27.3, which occurs when at most 1 observation is greater than or equal to 27.3.

The number of observations less than 27.3 follows a binomial distribution with n = 8 and p = 0.70.

P(Y₇ < 27.3) = P(at least 7 out of 8 observations < 27.3)
                = P(exactly 7 observations < 27.3) + P(exactly 8 observations < 27.3)
                = P(X = 7) + P(X = 8), where X ~ Binomial(8, 0.70)

**Calculating:**

P(X = 7) = C(8,7) × (0.70)⁷ × (0.30)¹
         = 8 × (0.70)⁷ × 0.30
         = 8 × 0.0823543 × 0.30
         = 0.197649

P(X = 8) = C(8,8) × (0.70)⁸ × (0.30)⁰
         = 1 × (0.70)⁸ × 1
         = 0.05764801

P(Y₇ < 27.3) = 0.197649 + 0.05764801
             = 0.25529701
             ≈ 0.255

Summary: The final answer is $0.255$
